caption: Don’t know why I didn’t know about this place- the food was just real good! The fried plantains with garlic crisped right on was delicious! Pollo con mole was tender and flaked right off the bone! Order up folks!

my friends & i came here on a Friday night and we were promptly seated on their outdoor dining area. Each table is divided from the other one with a clear plastic wall. There are heated lamps above each table as well. Overall, we were very comfortable and warm. We started off with chips & guac: 10/10. the portion was massive and the sweet sauce they give you on the side tastes so good mixed with the guac. I got the enchiladas and my friend got steak, everything was so delicious. In total we must have had 5 margaritas each, they were so delicious and we came at happy hour which was a plus :) overall this place is a great option if you’re looking for comfortable outdoor dining in nyc as well as delicious mexican food & drinks.

A hidden gem with decently priced food and good options. The backyard is nice and since the heated lamps are out front in the box-patio, they brought a portable one out for us. They even had vegan tacos (with oyster mushrooms).  The sweet plantains (maduros) and tostanos were good and the chicken quesadilla was okay but a little dry. One main negative though was how small of a serving their  margarita was (see pic) - they say it’s the same ounces but there’s a lot of ice in it so it wasn’t worth it.

We ordered takeout today... they forgot the burrito.  We called and they came back with it. ⭐️  Everything we ordered was fresh and delicious.   We will be ordering from here again as they are that good.   5 ⭐️ ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
Small family owned and operated spot. Great food. Great mezcal selection. Friendly staff. Sweet backyard. Baja fish tacos are a thing of beauty.

Authentic and delicious.  My wife and I have been here several times and have yet to try something we didn't love.  That's goes for the drinks as well!  Their mezcal drinks in particular are my personal favorites.  And to top it off?  Absolutely sweet and wonderful staff.  Great vibe, great food, great drinks.  Highly recommend

The enchiladas are the real deal. 99% of the bar is stocked with rare hard to find Tequilas you’ve never heard of. The people!!! Chips & Salsa! Guac! Queso Fondito!!!!!!!!! The Frozen Margaritas will knock your socks off but you have no idea. Huge backyard court yard. Faviola!
Excellent food!
All you can drink for 90 minutes
Delicious food and a warm environment in this family run resturant.
The food here was amazing I usually don’t eat as much but over here I ate SO MUCH the workers are extremely nice.
Friendly place with a homie feel
Best margarita I ever try in the restaurants  and guacamole was delicious 😋 great service
Authentic Mexican cuisine! This is my favorite Mexican hidden gem in Bay Ridge. Delicious, homemade options. It's family-run and their staff is super friendly. Definitely recommend!

How is this place not rated higher? So much flavor and way better food than the more popular Mexican restaurants in the area. The beet and orange tostada was unique and delicious. The pulled pork with pickled habanero was amazing. This place should be packed every day. Until then I’ll just keep enjoying Bay Ridge’s best kept secret.
Our favorite spot for Mexican food in Bay Ridge!
The food is consistently well prepared and yummy, workers hands out awesome service. I love how clean it is and atmosphere. Keep up the good work.
(Translated by Google) It is an excellent place and the attention is very good  (Original) Es un excelente lugar y la atención es muy buena

Nice backyard atmosphere. Delicious Food...Great Authentic Margaritas! The owner Veronica was eating dinner there as well, which is always a good sign to me.  We had great service from Ivy and Louie. Will definitely be back soon.
Always perfect for food and drinks. They helped us survive the pandemic. Lovely outdoor dining and indoor dining.

Today I got a table here and suddenly they needed my table for a “reservation.” Just because I was by myself and all the other tables were in big groups. I felt picked on. So I had to leave and I did not finish my food.  The drink I ordered didn’t even arrive to my table yet and they initially wanted to charge the drink that I never had. They offered it as a complimentary drink after but I did not want anything to do with it.  I used to love everything about this restaurant because it was a local business by my house... but now I will never come here ever again.

The atmosphere is great, the waiters are friendly and make you feel welcomed. The backyard makes you feel like if your actually in Mexico. They make homemade tortillas. The  first time I went I ordered  steak tacos, they were very good. I also had frozen tamarin margarita, it was okay, very strong with liquor. I was not crazy for the memelas, not enough cheese, maybe? The tres leches cake was super sweet. I will be going back to taste other dishes.

bad service. I ordered two bistec tacos with extra guac on both tacos and i was charged 1 dollar extra for guac on each taco so i had to pay 2 extra dollars. Once I open the takeout box, it wasn't  there. Cashier and chef did not wear a mask. food was ok.
The food and drinks were delicious! Thoroughly enjoyed our night out in their backyard outdoor seating. Portions are nice and prices are right. An absolute new favorite. I hope to come often
Love this place, the food is amazing!

I ordered pickup on uber eats. We ordered bistec burrito, baja shrimp tacos,  elotes and the chocolate hazelnut tres leches cake. When I went to pick up the order, the elote and the cake were both missing from the order which I luckily spotted and was able to get them before I left. I was immediately turned off that half of my order was missing but once I got home and tried the food my entire opinion was reversed. Absolutely DELICIOUS!!!! The corn tortillas used for the baja shrimp tacos were clearly homemade, the shrimp were plentiful. The elotes was well seasoned and had plenty of cotija cheese. The chocolate hazelnut tres leches was an absolutely triumph, probably the best chocolate cake I've ever tasted. I will be a repeat customer for sure. Do yourself a favor and definitely get the chocolate hazelnut tres leches.

Family owned spot with a very friendly, very lovely staff. Service is always great! They will accommodate your toddler and her messes. Their food is always high quality! We are a big fan of the chili rellenos and just about any of the plato's. And, that tequila and mezcal selection is perfection.

Bay Ridge, if you are not going here you're asleep! Plain and simple! This is great Mexican food and lovely service. If you want a relaxing atmosphere with chill music and atmosphere this is the place to go. When you wake up and get food grub let me know.

Braised beef - really, really good.
Good food, good margaritas - sometimes there's a long wait for drinks or food but I try to remember it's a small, family-run restaurant.

Good food and service. Interior has an impressive aesthetic, Mexican-style. There's also a nice outdoor space in the back for dining outside. If you like tequila and don't mind spending the money, they have a strong selection. The restaurant is a little pricey overall. A friend was annoyed that a service charge was already added to the bill without any warning. We came very close to adding a tip on top of that before we noticed. Summary: Nice place but in terms of value, there are better places all around the neighboring Sunset Park.

Well, my major concern was how the waiter implied that the Guac and Chips were something offered to all customers by stating "Can i start you off with chips and Guac?"  Well, the Guac and Chips are $11 each.  And he brought 3 servings for the table of 12.  So there was a $33 dollar deficit one person decided to eat!  So please beware.  Otherwise the food is above average.
We love Coszcal, where we always feel like part of the family. Great service. Delicious food. Amazing and inventive cocktails! Our favorite restaurant in Bay Ridge!
Went for brunch food was good but loved the bottomless drinks

Came here unexpectedly with friends last night and was pleasantly surprised!!   We sat in the patio area and dined on great quality, authentic Mexican food and the sangria was delicious too. Definitely will be back!!

Enjoyed everything about the experience. The Decour was inviting and relaxing. The personalized service is outstanding. The food and drink rounds out the overall excellent time. Enjoy.

I dined here yesterday with a large group of people, and the staff was extremely accomodating and the food was out of this world delicious.

Listen I can't even begin to describe how amazing the food is here. This is something you have to experience on your own. It is quite possibly the best Mexican spot I've tried and this is coming from someone who lived in CA for 5yrs and tried all types of Mexican food. This is the spot. Do yourself the favor and come here. You won't be disappointed. From the decor, the costumer service everything is on point. They deserve a 10 star rating!

The food was good and I was glad to find the margarita was not a mix for happy hour! I had 1 taco, 1 Gordita taco, and tostones, and I found them all good. My girlfriend had the slow cooked pork, and only complaint was the beans needed more flavor. Good experience. I wish the menu was a bit more detailed. And the young gentleman waiter was the best tonight.
Always great food and friendly service.

Don't do business with this restaurant. Held a wedding party in their back space. Their set price for rental, food, and drinks didn't include the salary for the waiters. They withheld this information. Didn't provide a contract. And couldn't agree amongst each other on what was covered and what wasn't. And when we disputed the hidden fees, the restaurant owners were condescending to the party and belittled people because of their ethnicity and social class. The daughter even went as far as to say that because she had a private school education, she knew best. It was a belittling and frustrating experience. Not to mention expensive. They ruined everyone's night.

Warm hospitality. A simple warm place with wonderful food and mixed drinks. The .mixed drinks are exceptional. Cant say enough good things about food quality and presentatio n.Best Mexican restaurant we've been to in NYC

Coszcal de Allende,  offers mouthwatering authentic  fresh Mexican food. This is a hidden gem in the heart of Bay Ridge. My personal favorites are the fish ceviche, plato de barro and  tasty cocktail drinks which are pleasantly crafted.
Love this place! Food is always consistently good and the drinks are hand crafted. I love the fact that it feels like an authentic neighborhood family restaurant.

This is one of my go-to's in Bayridge. The food is quick, delicious, and reasonably priced. The service is good. It's a quaint little out of the way spot with a really nice walled off back patio. Relaxing vibe and a good selection of drinks. Perfect place for a hot summer day and there will be little other people around to bother you. I'd tell more people about it, but I almost want it to stay off the radar.
